This review was a really good one, before the insane DRM was introduced. I am a frequent traveler and I often happen to be in places without any internet connection. So prior to v2.5.1 of this emulator it was all right because the license check happened only at first launch. And after that, I could just never unload the app from the memory and it didn't require any network connection. After version 3.0 it has become just unbearable, because the license check is happening on EACH game launch. I always thought that emulators should work offline as it is the EMULATOR of a GAME CONSOLE. Even worse, after the newer updates - v3.1 or something like that, the application REQUIRES access to your locations and USES GPS ALL THE TIME. That is so unnecessary and a huge battery killer. It is really sad to see that, but if you, the developer, read this, please realize, that honest buyers are suffering because of all those insane license checks. For me it is impossible to use the app even though I bought it for the full price. If only it could be possible to go back to 2.5.1 at least... I would be glad... Until then.... I have spent dollars for the app I can not use. That is not fair.

Just to get this out of the way first.. I am running this on a Samsung Galaxy Note 9 128GB version which to be fair is a beast of phone and it has the storage to hold many PS2 ISO's at once.... So far it has played every single ISO ive thrown at it. I've collected many BIOS files over the years as well and all BIOS versions tested work without issues. I suspect most bad reviews fall in the "bad bios" or "corrupted ISO" or no ISO at all. I luckily had previously tested all my ISO's recently so I knew they were all valid and in good shape. My advice is to make sure of 3 things before you try this app... The first being sure that you are using a device that is FULLY capable of playing all PS2 games with ease at any Framerate. The second is to make sure you test it on a known good Iso. if you have a PC with the PCXS emulator installed test your ISO with that, if it runs with the BIOS you use with PCXS then it will work with this. The last item is mentioned before this. YOU MUST HAVE A PS2 BIOS IN ORDER TO USE THIS OR ANY PS2 EMULATOR. if your PS2 BIOS works with PCXS it will work with this. Valid BIOS files have a .Bin extension. Thats it. Hope this helps

I knew this app was too good to be true, so bought this and installed on my nvidia sheild tv pro, which is the most powerful android tv box out on the market. People online say that this works great with lots of ps2 games, but they did not say one important thing. For phones, you would not need Bluetooth controllers, but for Android TV Box's, you do. This is NOT compatible with Nvidia Sheild TV Controllers or Dualshock 3/4 Controllers. Needs specific HID controllers to work. Also, even if I do load PS2 games, it only works with low-graphic intensive PS2 games, for example. Kingdom Hearts 1, 2, Birth By Sleep, Final Fantasy, god of war. They work at a Low FPS and its a terrible game experience. They should update the app description saying the compatibility with Bluetooth controllers. And also that it works for THESE types of games, which should probably have a list as well.

When I first came across this PlayStation 2 emulator application, my first reaction was another one of those fake PlayStation 2 emulators that I came across the Google Play store except for Play! which was the only and legitimate emulator at the time and then I realized that it's charging $10 For it.  Because of that, my first word to describe it is its a "scam".  But then I started reading the user reviews and was pleasantly surprised that it's receiving positive reviews and ratings and that the reviewers are saying that it works but is in early stages of development but it works and is playable for a few games hence the description says 15% of them is playable.  And so I went ahead and took the risk in purchasing it.  To my surprise, it works!  And is a lot better than Play!  But it's in early stages of development and will continue to improve as updates go on and I was surprised on how well it runs in the early stages.  I was playing FFX and GOW and its playable.  I'm running on the Samsung Galaxy Note 8 which has the latest and greatest hardware on any smartphone and so I will run the emulator fairly well when the emulator is optimized.  I'm very satisfied with my purchase and will continue to support the development, hopefully they don't abandon it.  It's definitely a dream come true, finally playing PlayStation 2 games on the go and can't wait to fully play them when DamonPS2 Pro is optimized and is playable.  Thanks again DamonPS2 team for making a working PlayStation 2 emulator although you guys have a long road ahead to go for the emulator to become fully playable.  I'm hoping by the end of 2018 it's fully playable.

content: Played 3 games using this emulator (on my Essential PH-1), .Hack//Infection, Persona 3 FES, and IGPX. Both IGPX and P3 FES suffered from stuttering during the animated sequences. .Hack// and P3 FES suffered from texture and text glitches. IGPX was the worst of the 3 as the screen had some tearing and glitches, and the matches wouldn't even load, the game would just crash as the race started. Overall they all did really well as far as FPS is concerned but this emulator definitely needs more work done before a lot of games are both playable and enjoyable. But, this is an amazing start, and this is most likely the best PS2 emulator currently out. Looking forward to Future updates.
